      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. but wouldn't you say the R2P doctrine itself was a success since it actually prevented a massacre in benghazi at the time? it feels like u might be judging the whole thing based on the messy aftermath rather than if the intervention actually did what it was supposed to do when it happened.",
